article.headline: Wichita St. 64, Illinois St. 58
article.story: WICHITA, Kan. -- Toure Murry scored 16 points and Aaron Ellis added a season-high 14 as Wichita State defeated Illinois State 64-58 Wednesday night. The Shockers (8-11, 2-6 Missouri Valley) trailed 51-50 with 2:43 remaining, but consecutive 3-pointers by Murry and A.J. Hawkins and Murry sparked a 10-0 run that helped secure the win. Osiris Eldridge led Illinois State (16-3, 5-3) with team highs of 16 points and seven rebounds. Lloyd Phillips added 14 points for the Redbirds, including 12 in the second half. Wichita State trailed 28-21 at halftime but scored the first 12 points of the second period to go ahead 33-28. Ramon Clemente scored five of his 14 points during the Shocker run. Illinois State got back in it with 3-pointers and tied it at 44 with 7:57 remaining before the Shockers took charge again.
